The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Probables to be split into 2 groups
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Probables to be split into 2 groups
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) officials announced on Saturday that the selection committee has decided to split up the 45 Ranji Trophy probables into two groups of 20 and 25 players to facilitate practice and training methods.         
	Sambaran Banerjee, the newly appointed chief selector for the Bengal senior side, made an appearance during the Bengal probables practice session at the Eden and was seen in conversation with coach Utpal Chatterjee and consultant Mohinder Amarnath.         
	The two groups will practise on alternate days of the week, enabling selectors to monitor each cricketers performance better.         
	It has also been learnt that the pool of probable players will be retained for the upcoming season, opening up possibilities of players being rotated.         
	Sambaran, meanwhile, quipped: Well be following the players performances in the Snehanshu Acharya Challenger Trophy closely before picking the final Ranji squad.         
	Ranji Trophy will be the first assignment for new Bengal coach Utpal and consultant Amarnath.         
	Both have excelled as cricketers. Bengal, relegated to the Plate Group last season, are banking on the duos experience and expertise to get back to the Elite Group.                                                                                                                          
